### Lancer `$git config commit.template <chemin du fichier>` pour lier ce fichier aux commits
### ce fichier peut-être 'gité' ou alors le placer dans le dossier .git

# The commit message must follow this pattern: 
#  1. Begin with the team name in uppercase followed by a space
#  2. Preceded by a space and enclosed in square brackets, the PI number and the IT number linked by a hyphen
#  3. Preceded by a space and a '#', an uppercase letter identifying the type of commit: 
#    - S for a Story
#    - R for a Refacto
#    - F for a Fix
#  4. Preceded by a dash, the identifier of the associated V1 card (000000 if no associated card)
#  5. Preceded by a space and enclosed in square brackets, the name of the associated feature, if any
#  6. Preceded by a space, the commit description (story title if applicable)

OLDELPASO [32-1] #S-000000 - [Feature] Descr
#PEANUTS [32-1] #S-000000 - [Feature] Descr